+ (g - li-1),

(6)

where is a stabilization parameter. For the decay step of our update rule, we also consider scaling

the decay rate for each parameter proportionally to MSg. Parameters with a high RMS gradient

affect the dynamics of the network more, so it makes sense to decay them faster. RMSnorm is MSg

divided by its mean, resulting in a normalized version of MSg with a mean of 1:

RMS norm

